    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "CONCORDE - THE SUPERSONIC PASSENGER JET\nFrancs",
      "Braniff flies the Concorde between Dallas-Fort Worth\nand Washington, D.C., at just under the speed of sound\n(Mach 0.95 or 650 mph). This is the first and only Concorde\nservice within the United States.\nFrom Washington the Concorde continues on to London or\nParis at twice the speed of sound (Mach 2.0 or 1,350 mph).\nThis is the only same-day service from mid-America to\nBritain and Europe.\nBRANIFF INTERNATIONAL\nThe only U.S. airline to fly Concorde.\n2015.166.2569"
    ],
